Implement a simulated live replay feature for the CyberNova Streamlit dashboard.

Do not replace the existing historical dataset. Add a separate live stream queue dataset and progressively reveal rows from it during dashboard runtime.

Requirements:

1. Create or support a file called data/live_stream_queue.csv
- It should contain about 30,000 synthetic IIS-style log rows.
- The rows should cover the next 14 days from the project demo date.
- It must use the same columns as the main enriched CyberNova dataset where possible.
- Include timestamp, date, time, ip_address, method, uri, status_code, user_agent, country, service, segment, is_bot, is_warm_lead, campaign, opportunity_value, response_time_ms, bytes_sent, and funnel_stage where available.

2. Add Live Replay Mode to the dashboard
- Add a toggle called “Live replay mode”.
- When off, the dashboard uses only the historical dataset.
- When on, the dashboard combines the historical dataset with the currently released live rows.

3. Progressive row release
- Use Streamlit session_state to track how many live rows have been released.
- Every refresh, add the next batch of live rows from live_stream_queue.csv.
- Use a safe default batch size, e.g. 50 to 200 rows per refresh.
- Add replay speed options: Slow, Normal, Fast.
- Do not require the user to wait two weeks. This is a simulated replay.

4. Auto refresh
- Refresh the dashboard every 3 to 5 seconds while live replay mode is active.
- If streamlit_autorefresh is available, use it.
- If not available, implement a safe fallback that does not crash.

5. Dashboard recalculation
- All KPIs, charts, filters, warm lead counts, service demand charts, country rankings, and executive summaries must use the combined dataframe when Live Replay Mode is active.
- Existing filters must still work.

6. Add a Live Feed Evidence Panel
Show:
- Live mode status
- New rows added this session
- Total rows currently visible
- Last log timestamp
- Last URI
- Last country
- Last status code
- Replay speed

7. Add a visible label
Use this wording:
“Simulated live replay using synthetic IIS logs”

8. Defensive coding
- Do not crash if live_stream_queue.csv is missing.
- If missing, show a warning: “Live stream queue not found. Generate live data first.”
- Do not duplicate large code blocks.
- Reuse existing loading and filtering functions.
- Keep the app deployable on Streamlit Community Cloud.

Acceptance criteria:
- The dashboard can run normally without live replay.
- When live replay is enabled, new rows appear gradually.
- KPIs update as live rows are released.
- A screenshot can prove live rows processed, last refresh time, and changing metrics.
- The feature is clearly labelled as simulated live replay using synthetic data.